imperturbable: Calm, not able to be upset or agitated
impassive: Not having or not showing physical feeling or emotion
imperious: Commanding, domineering; acting like a high-ranking person; urgent
impasse: Position or road from which there is no escape; deadlock
impermeable: Impassable, not allowing passage through (such as by a liquid)
imbue: Permeate or saturate, as dye in a fabric; influence throughout
ignoble: Not noble; having mean, base, low motives; low quality
impervious: Impenetrable, not able to be harmed or emotionally disturbed
